default“
default“
defaultParagraph 26. The
default 
defaultGovernment
default has calculated that even if customers of large retailers increase their paper bag use by 50% there would still be a negligible environmental impact in terms of carbon emissions (
default3,500default tonnes
default CO
default2
default equivalent
default 
defaultrepresenting less than 4% of the savings from plastic bagsdefault) due to the very low current levels of use
